{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"wait"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mutex"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using condition variables, it is possible that a spurious wakeup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may occur (ie: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" returns even though ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_signal()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" was","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not called).  It’s also possible that a stolen wakeup may occur."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_signal()"},{"text":" is called, but another thread acquires","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mutex"},{"text":" before this thread and modifies the state of the program in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such a way that when ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is able to return, the expected","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"condition is no longer met.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For this reason, "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must always be used in a loop.  See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the documentation for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" for a complete example."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/condref\/wait(mutex:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/wait(mutex:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef\/CondProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib12CondProtocolPAAE4wait5mutexyqd___tAA05MutexC0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7CondRefV","title":"wait(mutex:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"wait"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mutex"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"extendedModule":"GLib"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Atomically releases ","type":"text"},{"code":"mutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and waits until ","type":"text"},{"code":"cond","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is signalled."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When this function returns, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mutex"},{"text":" is locked again and owned by the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling thread."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondRef/CondProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\